  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.15.0\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nAfter upgrading to hardhat 2.15.0, toolbox 3.0.0 with ethers v6.6.0 I get an error for `block.timestamp` that `block` could be `null`.\r\nIs that intentional ?\r\nWhat is the best way to handle that ?\r\n\r\n![HardhatEthersProvider getBlock](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/assets/25609/08b35bbb-fd01-4b94-a98f-fc9c9d6d26f8)\r\n\r\n![block-is-possibly-null](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/assets/25609/0b767768-26e7-48a4-b399-2393f7acc329)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\nsee code example\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\n_No response_",
